<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-04-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-04-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="291" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                    <head>No. 287.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Stallo</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-04-09"><hi rend="italic">April</hi> 9,
                            1886</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Stallo is informed by Mr. Bayard that it is his desire that he should
                        attend the conference for the protection of industrial property to be held
                        at Borne on April 29, 1886. He is instructed to state that his presence is
                        merely consultative and wholly <hi rend="italic">ad referendum.</hi></p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>